<h1 class="title">Libertarianism-more-effective-in-complicated-societies</h1>
<p>
Perhaps surprisingly, libertarianism is more effective &#x2013; compared to the alternatives &#x2013; the more complicated the society.  <a href="Libertarianism-is-bottom-up.html#ID-DC6FE356-6E8C-4A1A-98E2-974F2FB74751">Libertarianism-is-bottom-up</a> and decentralized. The alternatives all involve more centralized planning. The more complicated the society, the less central planning will be effective at optimizing (and exploring) potential solutions.
</p>


